<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2321</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr>  <route>erct-000Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sections and retractions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>.</p></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2322</anchor> <rss>erct-000Z.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-000Z</addr>  <route>erct-000Z.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Functions and inverses</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>2323</anchor> <rss>erct-0014.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0014</addr>  <route>erct-0014.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homotopy</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0014.agda" type="external">erct-0014.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f , g  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } Bx</tex> be two dependent functions. A <em><strong>homotopy</strong></em> from <tex>f</tex> to <tex>g</tex>, writing <tex>H \colon  f  \sim  g</tex> is given by a dependent function <tex>H \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } fx=gx</tex>. We shall write <tex>1_{ f } \colon  f  \sim  f</tex> for the <em><strong>identity homotopy</strong></em> on <tex>f</tex> defined by <tex>1_{ f } x: \equiv   \mathsf {refl}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>2324</anchor> <rss>erct-002I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002I</addr>  <route>erct-002I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002I.agda" type="external">erct-002I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be maps equipped with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> <tex>s_f \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>s_g \colon  C \to  B</tex>. The composite <tex>s_f \circ  s_g \colon  C \to  A</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 The witness of sectionhood is defined using the witnesses for the two sections.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb></trail> <anchor>2325</anchor> <rss>erct-002J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002J</addr>  <route>erct-002J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002J.agda" type="external">erct-002J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be maps equipped with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> <tex>r_f \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>r_g \colon  C \to  B</tex>. The composite <tex>r_f \circ  r_g \colon  C \to  A</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 The witness of retractionhood is defined using the witnesses for the two retractions.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>5</crumb></trail> <anchor>2326</anchor> <rss>erct-0025.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-0025</addr>  <route>erct-0025.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>27</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Retract</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0025.agda" type="external">erct-0025.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>When <tex>s \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a section of <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>, we say that <tex>A</tex> is a <em><strong>retract</strong></em> of <tex>B</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>6</crumb></trail> <anchor>2327</anchor> <rss>erct-000U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr>  <route>erct-000U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>7</crumb></trail> <anchor>2328</anchor> <rss>erct-002K.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002K</addr>  <route>erct-002K.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002K.agda" type="external">erct-002K.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is biinvertible, with sections and retractions given by <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb></trail> <anchor>2329</anchor> <rss>erct-002L.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002L</addr>  <route>erct-002L.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002L.agda" type="external">erct-002L.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> maps. Then the composite <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex> is quasi-invertible, with sectionhood and retractionhood witnesses given by those of the <link href="erct-002I.xml" type="local" title="Composition of sections">composites of the component sections</link> and <link href="erct-002J.xml" type="local" title="Composition of retractions">retractions</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>9</crumb></trail> <anchor>2330</anchor> <rss>erct-000V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000V</addr>  <route>erct-000V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Equivalence of types</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000V.agda" type="external">erct-000V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>equivalence</strong></em> from <tex>A</tex> to <tex>B</tex> is defined to be a function <tex>A  \to  B</tex> equipped with a  <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinverse</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>10</crumb></trail> <anchor>2331</anchor> <rss>erct-000X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr>  <route>erct-000X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>11</crumb></trail> <anchor>2332</anchor> <rss>erct-003C.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Observation</taxon> <addr>erct-003C</addr>  <route>erct-003C.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003C.agda" type="external">erct-003C.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> The <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to <tex>f</tex> is simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link>.</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>12</crumb></trail> <anchor>2333</anchor> <rss>erct-000W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr>  <route>erct-000W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>13</crumb></trail> <anchor>2334</anchor> <rss>erct-001Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-001Q</addr>  <route>erct-001Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Fiber</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Q.agda" type="external">erct-001Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The <em><strong>fiber</strong></em> of a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> at an element <tex>b:B</tex> is the type consisting of elements <tex>a \colon  A</tex> equipped with identifications <tex>p \colon  fa=b</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related/> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2335</anchor> <rss>erct-003C.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Observation</taxon> <addr>erct-003C</addr>  <route>erct-003C.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>3</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-003C.agda" type="external">erct-003C.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> The <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to <tex>f</tex> is simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link>.</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2336</anchor> <rss>erct-002Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr>  <route>erct-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. Because <link href="erct-0026.xml" type="local" title="Propositions are closed under retracts">propositions are closed under retracts</link>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, which <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" title="Contractible types are propositions">follows</link> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2337</anchor> <rss>erct-002R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002R</addr>  <route>erct-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">Retractions</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002R.agda" type="external">erct-002R.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of some <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 Analogous to the <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" title="Sections of sections are unique">corresponding result for sections of sections</link>, using the fact that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> can be seen to be a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>- \circ  f</tex> at <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2338</anchor> <rss>erct-002O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002O</addr>  <route>erct-002O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Pushforward along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002O.agda" type="external">erct-002O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the postcomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f \circ  - \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  A \right ) \mathclose {} \to   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  B \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>The <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section and retraction</link> are built using by postcomposing with the designated <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section and retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>; the witnesses for the postcomposition <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections and retractions</link> are constructed using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for function spaces</link>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2339</anchor> <rss>erct-002F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002F</addr>  <route>erct-002F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002F.agda" type="external">erct-002F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a retraction <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. To construct <tex>h_r \colon  r \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> exhibiting <tex>r</tex> as a retraction of <tex>f</tex>, we use the identification between any two elements of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>fx</tex>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2340</anchor> <rss>erct-002G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002G</addr>  <route>erct-002G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002G.agda" type="external">erct-002G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a section <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. The witness <tex>h_s \colon  f \circ  s \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibiting <tex>s</tex> as a section of <tex>f</tex>, we use the second component of the centre of contraction.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2341</anchor> <rss>erct-002I.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002I</addr>  <route>erct-002I.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002I.agda" type="external">erct-002I.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be maps equipped with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> <tex>s_f \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>s_g \colon  C \to  B</tex>. The composite <tex>s_f \circ  s_g \colon  C \to  A</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 The witness of sectionhood is defined using the witnesses for the two sections.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2342</anchor> <rss>erct-002J.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>erct-002J</addr>  <route>erct-002J.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Composition of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002J.agda" type="external">erct-002J.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> and <tex>g \colon  B \to  C</tex> be maps equipped with <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> <tex>r_f \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>r_g \colon  C \to  B</tex>. The composite <tex>r_f \circ  r_g \colon  C \to  A</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>g \circ  f \colon  A  \to  C</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 The witness of retractionhood is defined using the witnesses for the two retractions.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2343</anchor> <rss>erct-0023.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0023</addr>  <route>erct-0023.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>22</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0023.agda" type="external">erct-0023.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A suitable <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" title="Univalent reflexive graph">univalent reflexive graph</link> on <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> to a fixed function <tex>r \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is given by a <link href="erct-0036.xml" type="local" title="Contravariant sum of fibrant families of univalent reflexive graphs">contravariant sum of univalent reflexive graphs</link>, as <link href="erct-001Y.xml" type="local" title="The standard cleaving for sectionhood witnesses">sectionhood witnesses are fibrant over their underlying sections</link>. In particular, an isomorphism of sections of <tex>r</tex> from <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s,h \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> to <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( s',h' \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is given by a homotopy <tex>H_s  \colon  s  \sim  s'</tex> together with a higher homotopy <tex>H_h  \colon  h  \sim   \mathopen {} \left ( \lambda x \mathpunct {.} \mathsf {ap}_{ r } \mathopen {} \left ( H_s x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  h'x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2344</anchor> <rss>erct-0024.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-0024</addr>  <route>erct-0024.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>22</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0024.agda" type="external">erct-0024.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A suitable <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" title="Univalent reflexive graph">univalent reflexive graph</link> on <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> to a fixed function <tex>s \colon  B  \to  A</tex> is given by a <link href="erct-0036.xml" type="local" title="Contravariant sum of fibrant families of univalent reflexive graphs">contravariant sum of univalent reflexive graphs</link>, as <link href="erct-0039.xml" type="local" title="The standard cleaving for retractionhood witnesses">retractionhood witnesses are fibrant over their underlying sections</link>. In particular, an isomorphism of retractions of <tex>s</tex> from <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( r,h \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> to <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( r',h' \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is given by a homotopy <tex>H_r  \colon  r  \sim  r'</tex> together with a higher homotopy <tex>H_h  \colon  h  \sim   \mathopen {} \left ( \lambda x \mathpunct {.} H_r \mathopen {} \left ( r x \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  h'x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2345</anchor> <rss>erct-001Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Example</taxon> <addr>erct-001Y</addr>  <route>erct-001Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The standard <link href="erct-0032.xml" type="local" title="Fibrant family of univalent reflexive graphs">cleaving</link> for <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sectionhood</link> witnesses</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Y.agda" type="external">erct-001Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a given function. Given a <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> <tex>H \colon  s \sim  s' \colon  B \to  A</tex> and a witness <tex>h \colon  f \circ  s'  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> that <tex>s'</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>, we may construct a witness <tex>H^*h \colon  f  \circ  s  \sim 1_{ B }</tex> that <tex>s</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of <tex>f</tex> as follows:</p><tex display="block">
  H^*h x : \equiv   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( Hx \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  h x
</tex><p>As we evidently have <tex>1_{ s } ^*h x =  \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathsf {refl} \cdot  h x = h x</tex>, the data above constitute a <em>cleaving</em> of <tex>f \circ- \sim 1_{ B }</tex> over <tex>B  \to  A</tex>, both with their <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" title="Dependent product of univalent reflexive graphs">standard univalent reflexive graph structure</link> as given by (dependent) <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopies</link>. In this sense, sectionhood witnesses constitute a <link href="erct-0032.xml" type="local" title="Fibrant family of univalent reflexive graphs">fibrant family</link> of <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" title="Univalent reflexive graph">univalent reflexive graphs</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2346</anchor> <rss>erct-0039.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Example</taxon> <addr>erct-0039</addr>  <route>erct-0039.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The standard <link href="erct-0032.xml" type="local" title="Fibrant family of univalent reflexive graphs">cleaving</link> for <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractionhood</link> witnesses</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001Y.agda" type="external">erct-001Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a given function. Given a <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> <tex>H \colon  r \sim  r' \colon  B \to  A</tex> and a witness <tex>h \colon  r' \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> that <tex>r'</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>, we may construct a witness <tex>H^*h \colon  r  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex> that <tex>r</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> as follows:</p><tex display="block">
  H^*h x : \equiv  H \mathopen {} \left ( fx \right ) \mathclose {} \cdot  h x
</tex><p>As we have <tex>1_{ r } ^*h x = h x</tex>, the data above constitute a <em>cleaving</em> of <tex>- \circ  f \sim 1_{ B }</tex> over <tex>B  \to  A</tex>, both with their <link href="erct-001C.xml" type="local" title="Dependent product of univalent reflexive graphs">standard univalent reflexive graph structure</link> as given by (dependent) <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopies</link>. Thus retractionhood witnesses constitute a <link href="erct-0032.xml" type="local" title="Fibrant family of univalent reflexive graphs">fibrant family</link> of <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" title="Univalent reflexive graph">univalent reflexive graphs</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2347</anchor> <rss>erct-001S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001S</addr>  <route>erct-001S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>20</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Pushforward of <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" title="Univalent reflexive graph">univalent reflexive graphs</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001S.agda" type="external">erct-001S.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>If <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> has a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <tex>g \colon  B  \to  A</tex>, then a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" title="Univalent reflexive graph">univalent reflexive graph</link> structure on <tex>A</tex> induces a <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" title="Univalent reflexive graph">univalent reflexive graph</link> structure on <tex>B</tex>, setting <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( x  \cong _B y \right ) \mathclose {}  : \equiv   \mathopen {} \left ( gx \cong _A gy \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>We first prove the lemma for <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> functions, so that both the <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> are tracked by <tex>g</tex>. In this case, we may use <link href="erct-0016.xml" type="local" title="Singleton induction">singleton induction</link> via the <link href="erct-001D.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for types">univalence principle for types</link> to restrict attention to the case that <tex>f</tex> is the identity map, and the result is immediate.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2348</anchor> <rss>erct-000U.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000U</addr>  <route>erct-000U.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Biinverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000U.agda" type="external">erct-000U.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>biinverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a pair of a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> to <tex>f</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>2349</anchor> <rss>erct-000X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr>  <route>erct-000X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>